links.slidetitle:
New Mexico Statute allows a customer 30 days from the date of purchase to complete the transfer of ownership of a vehicle or vessel.   

(Late Transfer Penalty (code 70) (66-3-103(B))
links.displaytext:
New Mexico Statute allows a customer 30 days from the date of purchase to complete the transfer of ownership of a vehicle or vessel.   

(Late Transfer Penalty (code 70) (66-3-103(B))

links.slidetitle:
AVOID FINES AND PENALTIES

Titling and registering a vehicle or vessel within the 30-day time frame will help the customer avoid late fines and penalties.
links.displaytext:
AVOID FINES AND PENALTIES

Titling and registering a vehicle or vessel within the 30-day time frame will help the customer avoid late fines and penalties.

links.slidetitle: When the customer receives a Notice of Additional Requirements Letter, they have 10 days to return with the required document or information to avoid late registration penalties and late transfer fees.
links.displaytext: When the customer receives a Notice of Additional Requirements Letter, they have 10 days to return with the required document or information to avoid late registration penalties and late transfer fees.

links.slidetitle:
What if a customer waits until the last minute?
If a customer comes in near the end of the 30-day period and has to return because of missing documents or information, he will probably be charged the late transfer fee.
links.displaytext:
